      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "To be clear: a bitcoind crash _cannot_ cause this. It is possible for the wallet to be corrupted (which can often be salvaged with `-salvagewallet`) but not deleted. It is not possible for `bitcoind.conf` to be corrupted or deleted in a crash as that file is never written by the code at all, just read at start.\n",
